<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-12T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-11T03:00:00-05:00" n="898" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d898">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 150.07/41</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Vancouver</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MRE1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Mansfield</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <dateline>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate General</hi>, <lb/>
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="italic">Vancouver</hi></placeName>, <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1914-08-12T09:00:00-05:00" notBefore="1914-08-11T00:00:00-08:00"><hi rend="italic">undated</hi></date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received August 12,
                                1914, 9 a.m.</hi>] </dateline>
                        <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                        <p>I have the honor to request instructions whether military reservists are
                            permitted transit through the United States. Am informed that the United
                            States immigration officers, Canada, have been instructed to pass number
                            French reservists whose transportation France provided for from one
                            Canadian point to another through the United States.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_MRE1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mansfield</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>